snippet.textDisplay: Not actually going to watch this, but if they said the things in the thumbnail, hyperbole much? Damn, talk about being overrated. 01 Miami produced more hall of famers than the last 20 years of Alabama football. There is no way this LSU team does that. Burrow is lot like Mayfield and Manziel, he looks good in college throwing bombs, but he isn’t complete enough for the NFL. All the draft guys keep telling us, but we don’t listen. He will probably go 1 because of the hype, but he’s really a third rounder. If I were the Bengals I would be looking to move down and hopefully still get Herbert or Fromm. I was impressed with the receiving core for LSU though, a couple late first rounders there, but not a lot else caught my eye. I would even go so far as to say that was not Clemsons best effort and they left a lot of points on the field due to shooting themselves in the foot. They also should have went two high safeties early on when it was apparent LSU couldn’t run against their front seven. If the only weapon they have is a bomb, why not try and take it away? Poor coaching lost that game, not talent.
